# Knowledge Base

This folder documents the manually curated external knowledge base used in the MLLM-based historical plausibility review stage.

In this study, historical and architectural knowledge was manually collected, summarized, and organized by the researchers from academic literature, museum sources, historical painting studies, and architectural references. These curated knowledge entries were then provided to the MLLM as reference materials during the review process.

This repository does not claim to provide a fully automated RAG pipeline or a complete historical database. Instead, it provides representative knowledge sources, structured knowledge-entry examples, and the knowledge selection protocol used to support the knowledge-informed review.

Due to copyright and licensing restrictions, this repository does not redistribute full-text academic publications, books, or high-resolution museum images. The released materials are intended to improve procedural transparency and reproducibility by showing how external knowledge was organized and used in the review process.

# Knowledge Sources

The manually curated knowledge base was constructed from online and offline sources related to Song Dynasty architecture, urban life, historical painting analysis, and *Along the River During the Qingming Festival*.

